Baroka FC are starring down the relegation barrel after drawing 2-2 with Chippa United in a league match at the Nelson Mandela Bay stadium in Gheberha on Saturday afternoon. Bienvenu Evanga and Decide Chauke scored for Baroka, while Riaan Hanamub and Thokozani Sekotlong scored for Chippa. Baroka remains on the bottom of the log with 22 points in 28 matches, three points below Moroka Swallows with only two matches remaining. Chippa are in 13th position with 28 points in 28 matches. In the other PSL match, Marumo Gallants played to a goalless draw with Golden Arrows in Polokwane.